It's Business Etiquette Week!  Join us in enhancing professionalism and fostering positive relationships with these 5 key tips:  

1. Dress for Success: Present yourself professionally, reflecting your competence and confidence in every interaction.

2. Practice Active Listening: Give your undivided attention, demonstrate empathy, and truly understand others' perspectives.

3. Punctuality Matters: Value others' time by being punctual and respecting deadlines, meetings, and commitments.

4. Positive First Impressions: Make a lasting impact with a warm smile, firm handshake, and professional demeanor.

5. Show Appreciation: Express gratitude for colleagues' contributions, fostering a culture of recognition and teamwork.

Let's elevate our professionalism and build strong relationships through impeccable business etiquette!  #BusinessEtiquetteWeek #Professionalism #PolarisConsultingGroup

Today we expanded our substance use disorder grants through an additional $5.7 million in awards to our second phase of grantees. Each grant will address substance use disorder, focusing on at least one of the following themes: access to care, quality of treatment, and youth prevention and early intervention. 

This second phase of grants is a part of the $30 million we plan to invest through 2024 to make significant progress in addressing the mental health and well-being in our communities, with an emphasis on substance use disorders. To date, we have awarded more than $19.5 million. 

More on this phase of grants: https://medium.com/elevancehealthfoundation/elevance-health-foundation-grows-substance-use-disorder-partnership-programs-through-second-phase-cb088a072e06

This week, Gleaners Food Bank of Indiana Inc. received $450,000 from Anthem Blue Cross and Blue Shield Foundation, a philanthropic arm of Elevance Health Foundation, to continue its the Food as Medicine program. The program, which is a Feeding America initiative funded by the Foundation, will help connect people facing hunger to food distribution programs that provide access to healthy food options. 

Read more: https://www.greensburgdailynews.com/news/gleaners-food-bank-of-indiana-receives-450-000-grant/article_533f5032-1446-11ee-8002-871949ed55e2.html

Each year, we partner with the American College of Sports Medicine to unveil the ACSM American Fitness Index. The Fitness Index ranks the 100 largest cities in the U.S. and provides each city with a detailed view of where they are succeeding and where improvements are needed. 

Six out of 10 American adults have a chronic disease, and four out of 10 have two or more. This year's Fitness Index highlights the prevalence of chronic diseases in our country and makes the case for physical activity as an effective way to address them. We also know that food is medicine, and consistent access to nutritious food is an essential part of maintaining health. Proper nutrition, fitness, and health are deeply connected, and when we prioritize all three, we can improve our quality of life.

See the full rankings and see how your city scored here: https://medium.com/elevancehealthfoundation/elevance-health-foundation-and-american-college-of-sports-medicine-unveil-the-2023-acsm-american-fe5156983b9d

Bria, your unwavering commitment and dedicated effort have left an indelible mark. From the very first contact during the interview process, you've exemplified excellence. Your ability to make even the most challenging onboarding process seamless and stress-free is truly commendable. 🌠

Natalie, you are undeniably a treasure to our company. Your initial support and assistance during my early days at Polaris have not gone unnoticed. Your promptness and willingness to lend a helping hand with day-to-day tasks have created an uplifting work environment that everyone values. 🌻

Aaliyah, your tireless dedication to ensuring our business remains compliant with vital HR duties is beyond remarkable. Your commitment to keeping us on track is truly inspiring. Your contribution to the team does not go unnoticed – your hard work is a driving force behind our collective success. 🌐

And let's not forget to acknowledge Mr. Gaylord for his exceptional leadership and his role in creating a dynamic team. Being a part of this team under his guidance has been an absolute pleasure. Here's to his continued success and the bright journey ahead! 🏆

Let's embrace this wonderful spirit of appreciation and continue to support each other as we strive for greatness together! 🤝🌈 #TeamAppreciation #PolarisConsultingGroup

This strong growth suggests new opportunities will emerge, especially in the #crossborder environment as more #countries awaken to the convenience, speed and security of #onlineshopping.

It’s been a great first day here at Tottenham Hotspur Stadium for Fintech Week London 2023! The brightest minds and industry leaders have come together to address challenges and changes in #fintech. 
 
We ended the morning hearing from Himal Makwana, FIS SVP Platforms, on a panel discussing whether or not #embeddedfinance is a threat, opportunity or paradigm shift. Then we got the afternoon started with Silvia Mensdorff-Pouilly, FIS SVP Head of EMEA Corporates & International Banking, listening to her panel explore the role of fintech and innovative practices to accelerate the benefits of #ESG and its future impact for all. 
 
It’s been an incredible day and we’re looking forward to what insights tomorrow brings!

caption: As a founding member of the World Economic Forum's First Movers Coalition (FMC), we join pioneering companies across the aluminum value chain using their purchasing power to create early markets for innovative clean technologies. As a member of the coalition, we are committed to purchasing 10% of primary aluminum annually as low-carbon aluminum by 2030. Echoing the goals of our Climate Transition Plan, the coalition advocates for industry alignment and #collaboration across the value chain to decarbonize the aluminum sector. Watch to learn more about Ball's advocacy goals as a part of the FMC.

When you think of multi-story multi-family buildings, does your mind automatically envision concrete and steel? It’s time to think again. 

Wood is not only suitable for multi-family buildings, but it also offers a number of benefits that make it equal to or better than other materials, in many cases.

These include:

✅ Full range of products, stocked locally
✅ Cost savings
✅ Versatility
✅ Carbon impact
✅ Meets fire requirements

Read our full article here: https://www.bc.com/blog/5-benefits-of-wood-in-multifamily-projects/

Today, we celebrate Juneteenth (or Freedom Day), a recognition of the resilience of the Black community as we embrace the legacy of those who fought for equality.

We're honored to have Beacon (our business resource group for the advocation, allyship and advancement of Black individuals and groups) co-workers participate in Juneteenth activities:

🌴 Greenville: TD SYNNEX and Beacon were participants and sponsors of the 2nd Juneteenth Royal Gala in Greenville, including a main stage speaking session with TD SYNNEX's Johnny Young

🏜️ Tempe: Beacon, in partnership with the Tempe Black Employee Alliance, participated in Tempe's 10th Annual Juneteenth - Reclaiming the Future community event 

🏖️ Clearwater: Our Clearwater and Greenville offices held a "Juneteenth: A Celebration of Freedom" panel event for co-workers to learn more about the history and impact of Juneteenth

caption:
Plains’ Earth Week Team Crosses Borders to Celebrate Our Planet

Plains celebrated Earth Day again this year by holding Earth Week 2023. There were many activities planned across North America, and all were made possible through the united efforts of the Earth Week team members. The team planned events all week, including educational fairs in Houston and Calgary as well as a well-respected and featured guest speaker Brian Keating, former Head of Conservation Outreach for the Calgary Zoo, to keep employees engaged and ensure the message of Earth Week reached staff across North America. Volunteer events like tree plantings were also offered to employees, and information was shared with all of Plains’ employees regarding what we do as a company to help the environment.

All of these efforts reflect our Core Value of Safety & Environmental Stewardship, which says “We conduct our business in a manner that is safe for our employees, business partners, communities and the environment.” Visit our Vision, Strategy and Values page at the link below to learn more about how Plains’ Core Values drive our operations. 

https://www.plains.com/about-us/vision-strategy-values

Yesterday, Feed More received $450,000 from Anthem Blue Cross and Blue Shield Foundation, a philanthropic arm of Elevance Health Foundation, to continue its Food as Medicine program. 

The program, which is a Feeding America initiative funded by the Foundation, will support Feed More's Health Initiatives Department as it develops partnerships with additional healthcare providers across Central Virginia, with a particular focus on Petersburg, the Tri-Cities, and rural communities.

Almost half a million adults in Virginia have a substance use disorder, and for than a decade, fatal drug overdoses fueled by opioids have been the leading cause of unnatural deaths in the Commonwealth.

That's one of the reasons why Anthem Blue Cross and Blue Shield Foundation, a philanthropic arm of Elevance Health Foundation, has granted $500,000 to help Virginia Association of Free & Charitable Clinics expand substance use disorder peer-based recovery programs in the Commonwealth to six clinics over the next three years.

More on this grant and its impact on the community: https://www.wdbj7.com/2023/08/31/roanoke-program-leading-way-substance-abuse-support-virginia/

June is National Safety Month, and we wrapped up our annual Health, Safety and Environmental (HSE) Week. This year’s theme was “Control the Hazard” and focused on the understanding and implementation of effective controls to protect individuals from hazards that can be found in the office or at home. 

Controlling hazards means:

🦺  Knowing how to spot hazards   
🦺  Knowing how to assess the risk of the hazard   
🦺  Taking actionable steps to limit or eliminate the hazards from the workplace or home 

Learn more about our safety programs at https://www.plains.com/sustainability/safety

During the month of July, our Next Meal campaign will plan activities around the world to help address the millions affected by food insecurity in our communities.

Marriott is proud to support United Way and Survivor Alliance in celebrating the life and legacy of anti-trafficking advocate Deborah Pembrook through the launch of The Pembrook Fellowship. http://marr.in/6182ON5z0

Consistent with Marriott's Serve360 efforts to empower through opportunity, the fellowship will build skills among survivors to lead the anti-trafficking movement and equip organizational partners with the tools needed to create trauma-informed, inclusive workplaces. During the program, fellows will go through leadership training, while receiving competitive part-time salaries, access to benefits, and other career growth opportunities. 

The Pembrook Fellowship will empower survivors of human trafficking and host organizations to shape the future of the anti-trafficking movement.

September is National Recovery Month, and with the CDC recently reporting an all-time high suicide rate, it’s never been more important to let people know that help is available.

That's why Anthem Blue Cross and Blue Shield Foundation, a philanthropic arm of Elevance Health Foundation, has awarded a three-year, $900,000 grant to Indiana Recovery Network, a program of Mental Health America of Indiana, which will allow for better access to mental health and substance use disorder resources in rural areas. Through this program, IRN will be able to fill “resource deserts” throughout Indiana to make sure that everyone has access to the help they need. 

Thank you Heather Rodriguez, Director at IRN, for sharing more about this program with Inside INdiana Business! https://www.insideindianabusiness.com/articles/creating-regional-recovery-hubs-in-indianas-mental-health-deserts

Cousins Faisal and Ehsan came to the U.S. from Afghanistan in 2021 and are currently associates at Marriott Bethesda Downtown at Marriott HQ. The two work as Banquet Housemen at the hotel with aspirations to become managers of the banquet division. 

They credit everyone at the hotel for helping them adjust to their first jobs. In fact, the pair have found a sense of belonging at Marriott by taking on new experiences. "We’ve been working here for over a year now. We enjoy it – it’s why we’re still here," said Faisal.

Meet Lidia, a native of Ukraine who fled her country due to the war. She is now an associate at Leipzig Marriott Hotel in Germany, where she works as a server. After just a year, she is nearly fluent in German and plans to enroll in hospitality school. 

At Marriott, Lidia has been able to find support in her new home. "From the very beginning, I was warmly welcomed and embraced by colleagues. Even though my family is far away from me now, the Leipzig Marriott team makes me feel like I have a second family."

Celebrating Success: DTRA OSBP Wins the DOD Verdure Award!
 
We are thrilled to share some fantastic news from the Defense Threat Reduction Agency's Office of Small Business Programs (DTRA OSBP)! 🌟 They have been honored with the prestigious DOD Verdure Award, recognizing their dedication to driving efficient buying practices and exceptional small business engagement.
 
At Polaris Consulting Group, Inc., we take immense pride in supporting DTRA OSBP and their incredible achievements. We would like to extend our heartfelt congratulations to the entire DTRA OSBP team for this well-deserved recognition! 👏
 
A special shout-out goes to our exceptional acquisition analysts, Nicole S. and Naomie L.! 🌠 Their unwavering commitment and invaluable contributions have played a crucial role in DTRA OSBP's success. Through their innovative efforts, they directly assisted with continued outreach among qualified small business vendors and incorporated small business considerations in formal market research, including the development of the Vetted Vendor Database.
 
Nicole and Naomie, your hard work and dedication have been recognized, and we are grateful to have you as part of our team at Polaris! 🚀 Your exceptional efforts reflect the true spirit of collaboration and excellence that we strive for.
 
Join us in celebrating this incredible achievement and expressing our heartfelt congratulations to DTRA OSBP, Nicole S., and Naomie L.! 🎉 We look forward to continuing our journey of success and making a positive impact together.
 
#DTRAOSBP #VerdureAward #TeamSuccess #TeamPolaris #Collaboration #Innovation #SmallBusinessEngagement #Congratulations
